content.description: Start with left hand on the sharp edge.  Right hand slightly further along the edge on a similar spot. Lower down and position yourself to put a left heel over the edge. Pull into the overhang to start the problem.  Right foot on the small edge underneath.   Right hand bump to the well defined pinch crimp.  Right toe hook behind left heel.  Bump left hand. Move heel to old left hand position.  Bump right hand just on top of the chip where there is a nice flat spot.  Left hand to the pinch crimp.  Left heel bumped.  Right toe hook underneath near start hold for Honey GoGo.  Left hand match with right hand. Bump right hand around corner edge.  Rotate left heel to toe to get reach to bump left hand.  Lock out cut feet to right heel on top of bolder. Use heel to assist mantle over the top of the boulder.
content.location: On the left side of the boulder get as close to the base of the edge as possible.  Use the edge to start.

content.description: Shaded trail side boulder. 3rd grouping of boulders on the North side of Route 1.  Very nice overhang boulder.
